      • saveTemp

        public java.lang.String saveTemp​(java.util.List<TemperatureData> temperatureData)
        saveTemp is used to save the continuous stream of Temperature data feeded from Live Monitoring Device using API.

        This Method will save the Single or Bulk data at once and return back response as success string if all the records have been saved successfully.

        Parameters:
        temperatureData - List of the Temperature data to be stored.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Input format of the data is not proper.

      • getHourlyData

        public java.util.List<MaterializedHourly> getHourlyData()
        getHourlyData is used to return the average of continuous stream of Temperature data per Hour feeded from Live Monitoring Device using API.

        This Method will fetch the average data at once from Materialized Views and returns the Average per Hour. These values are precalculated and already present in the tables.

        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Issue with Network/Database is down.

      • getDailyData

        public java.util.List<MaterializedDaily> getDailyData()
        getHourlyData is used to return the average of continuous stream of Temperature data per day feeded from Live Monitoring Device using API.

        This Method will fetch the average data at once from Materialized Views and returns the Average per day. These values are fetched by using the views and aggregating the retrieved data.

        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Issue with Network/Database is down.
